					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5842825#post-3802287</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5842825/scp-3316#post-3802287</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 16 May 2018 14:27:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Doctor Cimmerian</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1414765</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's one or both eyes. 395 would be if 3.4% of the population only had one eye go a fightin'.</p> <p>I think 1/400 is probably a little off considering there will be people with both eyes out for the night that will muck up the math a bit. Though the number is still incredibly high in comparison to the average number of eyes suffering serious injury during sleep elsewise. Which I imagine is non-zero but also pretty close to zero.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5842825#post-3801938</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5842825/scp-3316#post-3801938</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 16 May 2018 07:36:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DeRockProject</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>486453</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The population of Guttenberg is 11614 people. 3.4% of this is 395 eyes. Considering the minimum is 362 eyes, is the number of eyes very consistent?</p> <p>Averaging 10 minutes per fight, 34 eyes would be damaged. So after an event, 1 out of 400 people will have a damaged eye for seemingly no reason after a night, right?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
